    "body": "Sure. To reproduce first run `anvil -b 4`. Setting a block time ensures blocks are always being built and thus the base fee per gas is always adjusted even for empty blocks. Wait for a couple empty blocks until the fee is zero.\r\n\r\nRepro.sol:\r\n```solidity\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\ncontract Repro {\r\n    constructor() {\r\n        uint256 i = 0;\r\n        while (true) {\r\n            i++;\r\n            if (gasleft() < 100000) {\r\n                return;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nDeploy the above contract repeatedly using the following:\r\n```bash\r\nfor x in $(seq 1 1000); do\r\n  forge create --private-key 0xac0974bec39a17e36ba4a6b4d238ff944bacb478cbed5efcae784d7bf4f2ff80 Repro --gas-limit 25000000\r\ndone\r\n```\r\nThis will consume roughly 25 million gas per block. You can confirm this by examining `gasUsed` on incoming blocks.\r\nWhile the above contract deployments are running, inspect the base fee per gas in incoming blocks. The fee will be stuck at zero.",
